<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-08-11T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-08-11T16:00:00-05:00" n="732" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d732">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77/2635: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Warren</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-08-11T17:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">August 11,
                                        1922—5 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>87. Your No. 135, August 9, 1 p.m., received.</p>
                        <p>Referring to Department’s No. 73 of July 17, 3 p.m., American Ambassadors
                            at London, Paris and Rome are being instructed by telegraph formally to
                            present confidential memorandum to respective Foreign Offices. You will
                            please take similar action.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
